<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,258,1186]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Basal sclerotized curved expansion on gonocoxite; two pairs of arms of gonocoxites, one triangular with apical setulae and the digitiform ventral with rounded apex and a row of rod-like setae; one pair of subtriangular projection of aedeagal complex; fused apically envolving the aedeagus as a hood; ejaculatory apodeme twice the length of gonostylus; cercus with an apical expansion with two setulae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,258,1186]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,402,427]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Head subcircular in frontal view. Antenna incomplete in the studied specimens; scape subcylindrical; pedicel subspherical; basal flagellomeres pyriform and eccentric; ascoids 2.0 times as long as the length of flagellomere, annulated (
<figureCitation box="[583,690,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 A – H" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 39 A – H. Trichomyia pua sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Right wing; D. Cercus, in lateral view; E. Male terminalia, dorsal; F. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; G. Arm of gonocoxite; H. Male terminalia, lateral; I. Arm of gonocoxite with parameres (abbreviations: I, II agx = arm of gonocoxite I and II, gst = gonostylus, pac = projections in the aedeagal complex; pr = paramere)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262756/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[637,667,475,499]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). Palpus three segmented; first segment with sensilla in depressed pit on medial surface; palpus formula 1.0: 
<number box="[625,664,510,535]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="0.7">0.7</number>
: 
<number box="[667,705,510,535]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="0.5">0.5</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[722,826,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 A – H" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 39 A – H. Trichomyia pua sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Right wing; D. Cercus, in lateral view; E. Male terminalia, dorsal; F. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; G. Arm of gonocoxite; H. Male terminalia, lateral; I. Arm of gonocoxite with parameres (abbreviations: I, II agx = arm of gonocoxite I and II, gst = gonostylus, pac = projections in the aedeagal complex; pr = paramere)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262756/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[776,807,511,535]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
B
</figureCitation>
). Wing. R 
<number box="[942,950,525,539]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="2.0">2</number>
with base unsclerotized; R 
<number box="[1254,1262,525,539]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1271,1278,525,539]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="5.0">5</number>
incomplete at base; r-m and m-cu absent (
<figureCitation box="[459,561,549,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 A – H" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 39 A – H. Trichomyia pua sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Right wing; D. Cercus, in lateral view; E. Male terminalia, dorsal; F. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; G. Arm of gonocoxite; H. Male terminalia, lateral; I. Arm of gonocoxite with parameres (abbreviations: I, II agx = arm of gonocoxite I and II, gst = gonostylus, pac = projections in the aedeagal complex; pr = paramere)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262756/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[510,540,550,574]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
C
</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia: Hypandrium and gonocoxites fused with a basal sclerotized curved expansion. Two pairs of arms of gonocoxites, one digitiform, with rounded apex and a row of rod-like setae (
<figureCitation box="[159,265,621,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 A – H" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 39 A – H. Trichomyia pua sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Right wing; D. Cercus, in lateral view; E. Male terminalia, dorsal; F. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; G. Arm of gonocoxite; H. Male terminalia, lateral; I. Arm of gonocoxite with parameres (abbreviations: I, II agx = arm of gonocoxite I and II, gst = gonostylus, pac = projections in the aedeagal complex; pr = paramere)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262756/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[216,244,622,646]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
G
</figureCitation>
) and other triangular with an apical bristle, shorter than the dorsal. Gonostylus slightly sclerotized, articulated ventrally to gonocoxite, bare, truncated. Presence of one pair of subtriangular projection of aedeagal complex; fused apically envolving the aedeagus as a hood. One pair of parameres digitiform and projected laterally. Aedeagus bifid with truncated apex (
<figureCitation box="[720,912,729,754]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 A – H" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 39 A – H. Trichomyia pua sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Right wing; D. Cercus, in lateral view; E. Male terminalia, dorsal; F. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; G. Arm of gonocoxite; H. Male terminalia, lateral; I. Arm of gonocoxite with parameres (abbreviations: I, II agx = arm of gonocoxite I and II, gst = gonostylus, pac = projections in the aedeagal complex; pr = paramere)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262756/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Figs. 
<number box="[792,821,730,754]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
E, 
<number box="[860,890,730,754]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
H
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme twice the length of gonostylus. Epandrium wider than long, pilose. Cercus subtriangulares in lateral view with an apical expansion with two setulae (
<figureCitation box="[363,472,801,826]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 A – H" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 39 A – H. Trichomyia pua sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Right wing; D. Cercus, in lateral view; E. Male terminalia, dorsal; F. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; G. Arm of gonocoxite; H. Male terminalia, lateral; I. Arm of gonocoxite with parameres (abbreviations: I, II agx = arm of gonocoxite I and II, gst = gonostylus, pac = projections in the aedeagal complex; pr = paramere)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262756/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[419,449,802,826]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
D
</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct with apical micropilosity. Epiproct subcircular and membranous (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 39 A – H" captionStartId="63.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@63.[150,1436,339,1865]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="FIGURES 39 A – H. Trichomyia pua sp. nov. A. Scape, pedicel and basal flagellomeres; B. Palpus; C. Right wing; D. Cercus, in lateral view; E. Male terminalia, dorsal; F. Cerci, epandrium and hypropoct; G. Arm of gonocoxite; H. Male terminalia, lateral; I. Arm of gonocoxite with parameres (abbreviations: I, II agx = arm of gonocoxite I and II, gst = gonostylus, pac = projections in the aedeagal complex; pr = paramere)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262756/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,181,838,862]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" value="39.0">39</number>
F
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
